assignment:

This exercise is a variation over the [primitives cursor](/exercises/primitives-cursor/) exercise. Here you should record the cursor using glyphs from a font, starting from character 'a'. Try load an instance of [IBM Plex Mono](https://www.ibm.com/plex/), you'll find a .ttf file in the static folder. The sketch should accept the following inputs:
- a mouse click should clean the canvas
- the keyboard should inform the glyph drawn on the canvas
- the user should be able to adjust vertical and horizontal text alignment through two select controllers
- body size should be modified through a slider 
